HEADWORD: Ferme
<hw>Ferme</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> }</mhw><ety>[See <er>Farm</er>.]</ety> <def>Rent for a farm; a farm; also, an abode; a place of residence; <as>as, he let his land to <ex>ferm</ex></as>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Out of her fleshy <qex>ferme</qex> fled to the place of pain.</q> <rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fermacy</ent>⟦br⟧
